# |SUBJECT| <type>[optional scope]: <description>
# No more than 60 chars. Capitalize, but no punctuation.   # <-- Here is 60 chars

# Keep blank line between title and body.

# |BODY| Explain WHAT and WHY (not HOW). Include task ID (Jira or Git issue).
# ONLY write the BODY section IF the SUBJECT is not enough to clearly summarize the update/deletion/addition.
# Wrap at 72 chars.                                                    # <-- Here is 72 chars

# How to Write a Git Commit Message:
# https://chris.beams.io/posts/git-commit/
#
# 1. Separate subject from body with a blank line
# 2. Limit the subject line to 50 characters
# 3. Capitalize the subject line
# 4. Do not end the subject line with a period
# 5. Use the imperative mood in the subject line
# 6. Wrap the body at 72 characters
# 7. Use the body to explain what and why vs. how
#
# Additional source of information:
# https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/
